  "texts": [
    "While many arguments have been made for STAY, they mostly follow the same general pattern.",
    "That pattern is as follows:",
    "Without loss of generality, assume that you select Door 1, and that Monty then opens Door 3. 2.",
    "When Monty opens Door 3 that door of course has dropped out of consideration, and we are down to two doors, so the probability that the prize is behind Door 1 becomes 1 2; same as the probability that the prize is behind Door 2. 3.",
    "Hence there is no reason to switch doors (and since-as the economists who study rationality say-time is money, switching is irrational)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}